page.title: 02 DUNSWELL
page.content: Dunswell is small village only two miles away from Hull on the Hull-Beverley road (A1079).Although the flats of the nearby Hull council estate can be seen from Dunswell Lane, it is a different community entirely. There is little unemployment with upper to middle class occupations predominating. According to an unofficial survey about 600 people live in the 200 or so houses in Dunswell. The main village road is well known as an accident 'blackspot', though the only concession to passing traffic is a zebra crossing near the school.
